    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-12-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-12-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="223"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d223">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 493.11/457.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-12-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 19, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Chinese Government desires to pay each claim arising out of the revolution as
                    soon as it is allowed. The Diplomatic Corps has not <pb facs="0319" n="215"
                        xml:id="pg_215"/> yet reached a decision to accept immediate separate
                    payment of the claims. It may be difficult to secure payment of claims after the
                    sum of two million pounds sterling set aside for that purpose is exhausted.
                    Authority is requested to present each American claim immediately upon its
                    approval. It is further requested that the Legation be authorized to urge upon
                    the Diplomatic Corps to give priority to such claims as are founded on direct
                    and proximate results of the revolution.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
